quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  25,21,"And those who do not hope to meet us say, 'Unless the angels be sent down to us, or we see our Lord....!' They are too big with pride in their souls and they have exceeded with a great excess"
  25,22,"The day they shall see the angels,- no glad tidings on that day for the sinners, and they shall say, 'It is rigorously forbidden"
  25,23,"And we will go on to the works which they have done, and make them like motes in a sunbeam scattered"
  25,24,The fellows of Paradise on that day shall be in a better abiding-place and a better noonday rest
  25,25,"The day the heavens shall be cleft asunder with the clouds, and the angels shall be sent down descending"
  25,26,"The true kingdom on that day shall belong to the Merciful, and it shall be a hard day for the misbelievers"
  25,27,"And the day when the unjust shall bite his hands and say, 'O, would that I had taken a way with the Apostle"
  25,28,"O, woe is me! would that I had not taken such a one for a friend now"
  25,29,"for he did lead me astray from the Reminder after it had come to me, for Satan leaves man in the lurch"
  25,30,"The Apostle said, 'O my Lord! verily, my people have taken this Qur'an to be obsolete"
  25,31,Thus have we made for every prophet an enemy from among the sinners; but thy Lord is good guide and helper enough
  25,32,"Those who misbelieve said, 'Unless the Qur'an be sent down to him all at once...!' - thus - that we may stablish thy heart therewith, did we reveal it piecemeal"
  25,33,Nor shall they come to thee with a parable without our bringing thee the truth and the best interpretation
  25,34,"They who shall be gathered upon their faces to hell,- these are in the worst place, and err most from the path"
  25,35,"And we did give to Moses the Book, and place with him his brother Aaron as a minister"
  25,36,"and we said, 'Go ye to the people who say our signs are lies, for we will destroy them with utter destruction"
  25,37,"And the people of Noah, when they said the apostles were liars, we drowned them, and we made them a sign for men; and we prepared for the unjust a grievous woe"
  25,38,"And 'Ad and Thamud and the people of ar Rass, and many generations between them"
  25,39,"For each one have we struck out parables, and each one have we ruined with utter ruin"
  25,40,"Why, they have come past the cities which were rained on with an evil rain; have they not seen them?- nay, they do not hope to be raised up again"
  25,41,"And when they saw thee they only took thee for a jest, 'Is this he whom God has sent as an apostle"
  25,42,"he well-nigh leads us astray from our gods, had we not been patient about them.' But they shall know, when they see the torment, who errs most from the path"
  25,43,Dost thou consider him who takes his lusts for his god? wilt thou then be in charge over him
  25,44,"or dost thou reckon that most of them will hear or understand? they are only like the cattle, nay, they err more from the way"
  25,45,Hast thou not looked to thy Lord how He prolongs the shadow? but had He willed He would have made it stationary; then we make the sun a guide thereto
  25,46,then we contract it towards us with an easy contraction
  25,47,"And He it is who made the night for a garment; and sleep for repose, and made the day for men to rise up again"
  25,48,And He it is who sent the winds with glad tidings before His mercy; and we send down from the heavens pure water
  25,49,"to quicken therewith the dead country, and to give it for drink to what we have created,- the cattle and many folk"
  25,50,We have turned it in various ways amongst them that they may remember; though most men refuse aught but to misbelieve
  25,51,"But, had we pleased, we would have sent in every city a warner"
  25,52,So obey not the unbelievers and fight strenuously with them in many a strenuous fight